---
source: crates/cli/tests/integration/cli_help_test.rs
description: |
  Parity snapshot of `newton --help` after the cli-framework migration
  (issue #231).  The CHANGELOG references this artifact when describing
  the registered command surface that replaces the legacy clap dispatch.

  Lines under "Commands:" are sorted alphabetically; cli-framework returns
  them in HashMap order, which is non-deterministic across runs.
---
Usage: newton <COMMAND>

Commands:
  artifacts    Manage workflow output files and execution artifacts
  batch        Process queued work items for a project
  checkpoints  Manage and inspect workflow execution checkpoints
  completion   Emit shell completion script
  config       Inspect resolved Newton configuration
  doctor       Run local environment diagnostic probes
  dot          Generate a visual diagram of the workflow graph
  explain      Generate human-readable explanations of workflow behavior
  health       Print a one-line liveness status
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
  init         Initialize a Newton workspace with the default template
  lint         Check workflow for best practices and potential issues
  log          List and replay workflow execution history
  monitor      Monitor live ailoop channels via a terminal UI
  resume       Continue a workflow that was interrupted or stopped
  run          Execute a workflow graph
  serve        Start the Newton HTTP API server
  validate     Validate a workflow graph definition
  version      Print version information
  webhook      Run webhooks to trigger workflows from external events

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
